  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "The Renewable Energy for Resilient Agri-Food Systems (RERAS) project is a joint initiative of UNDP and the Government of Nepal, with funding from Norway, to increase food and nutrition security in western Nepal. RERAS is contributing to SDG 2: Zero Hunger and SDG 7: Affordable and Clean Energy, in Nepal’s most vulnerable regions.   By harnessing the transformative power of renewable energy, RERAS boosts agricultural production and dietary diversity to increase food  and nutrition security. The strength of RERAS lies in its diverse partnerships, bringing together expertise in climate resilient agriculture, off-grid renewable energy, home-grown school feeding and community empowerment."
    },
